transcript.text: Welcome to today's tutorial on creating a Template Properties Master in your own print shop store.
In this video, we'll guide you through the step by step process of setting up the Template Properties master to streamline your product design experience.
The Template Properties Master allows you to create the most extensively used template properties as a master.
For example, you can create a master for fonts, colors, layouts, etcetera to be displayed and used in the Designer Studio.
So let's dive in.
In the admin panel, navigate to the Template section.
There you will find a section for creating and managing Template Properties Master.
On this page, you can add, view, edit, and delete the master properties.
To find any properties by their type.
You can use this filter to get started.
Create a new property master by clicking on the Add button.
Give a title to the new property and select the store users for whom you are defining this property master.
Now it's time to define the property type.
Here we are creating a master for fonts.
So let's just select the fonts from the type drop down.
As soon as you select the type, you can choose the options.
Let's select the first four designer fonts as the master.
You will also have the option to select PDF fonts.
Once you are done with the selection, save the changes.
Similarly, you can create template master properties for other property types.
Next thing's how this master property is applied on specific templates.
For this, let's navigate to the product Templates section, select any template, then click on the action drop down and select Template Properties.
Let's assign the font master we created to this template.
Here you need to select the Template Property Master radio button, select the master title from the drop down and then save the changes on the front door.
When the customer selects the template and redirects to the Designer Studio, the master font you applied to the template will be available to the customers for personalization.
This was all about creating and assigning Template Property Master.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
